1 licensees.physicians.
2 (2) As required under section 16204, the board shall
3 promulgate rules requiring each applicant for license renewal to
4 complete as part of the continuing education requirement of
5 subsection (1) an appropriate number of hours or courses in pain
6 and symptom management.
7 (3) The board shall ensure that a continuing education course
8 or program on women's midlife health is available to a physician
9 that the physician may complete as part of the continuing education
10 requirement of subsection (1). A course or program described in
11 this subsection must include materials on communication and
12 physician preparedness in the management of menopause symptoms and
13 related chronic conditions. The board shall inform physicians of
14 courses or programs under this subsection and encourage physicians
15 to complete a course or program described in this subsection as
16 part of the continuing education requirement of subsection (1).
17 Sec. 17533. (1) Notwithstanding the requirements of part 161,
